EFF leader Julius Malema has been charged for allegedly shooting a firearm during a rally in the Eastern Cape last year. Courtesy #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - EFF leader Julius Malema and his bodyguard have been charged for allegedly shooting a firearm during a rally in the Eastern Cape last year. READ: Ten quotes from Malema ahead of elective conference EFF spokesperson Mbuyiseni Ndlozi claimed at the time that Malema had fired a toy gun and not a high-powered automatic rifle. The National Prosecuting Authority says Malema faces five counts, including unlawful possession of a firearm and ammunition. His bodyguard Adriaan Snyman has also been charged for unlawfully providing a firearm and ammunition to Malema. WATCH: EFF celebrates court win over Gordhan The case is scheduled for the 24th of February 2020